servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/curried-chickpea-and-butternut-squash-stew-673b9282fd3e9058428acb88
time required: 20 minutes
author: Sara Heilman
cuisine: South Asia
---

In a small #pot{}, combine @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, half the @veggie stock concentrate{2}, and @water{3/4%cup}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced into 1/2-inch pieces).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a medium pot over medium-high heat. Add onion, @butternut squash{8%oz}, and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are slightly softened and browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @chickpeas{1 can} and their liquid, @curry powder{1%tbsp}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, remaining stock concentrate, and @water{1/2%cup}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally and lightly mashing squash and chickpeas with a spoon, until squash is tender and liquid has slightly reduced, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

While stew cooks, roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}.

Toast @pita bread{2} until golden brown; spread with @butter{1%tbsp}. Sprinkle pitas with half the cilantro and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cut into quarters.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}.

Divide rice and stew between shallow #bowls{} in separate sections. Top stew with a dollop of @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} and remaining cilantro. Serve with buttery cilantro pitas on the side.

> This hearty vegetarian chickpea stew tastes like it's been cooking for hours! You'll simmer butternut squash, chickpeas, and onion together in a curry-spiced broth. Serve over fluffy, fragrant basmati rice and finish with a dollop of sour cream and sprinkle of cilantro with buttery toasted pitas alongside.